The Chairman of Fagge LGA of Kano State, Ibrahim Muhammed Abdullahi (Shehi), has called on the federal government to consider indigenes of his council while selling the recently built houses in the LGA under the National Housing Programme (NHP). The chairman made the call during a ceremony to hand over keys and documents to four beneficiaries that bought the houses from the federal government, noting that over the years, Fagge LGA had become a mini Nigeria as it housed the various tribes from across the country, hence the need to give it a special consideration to own majority of the houses in the estate. Fixing the power success key to Nigeria’s success CBN intervention didn’t disrupt impact of DBN within MSME space – Okpanachi He commended President Muhammadu Buhari for choosing Fagge for the construction of the houses, urging for more interventions “as people are now battling with getting property to live in.” Oh his part, the Minster of Works and Housing, Babatunde Raji Fashola, assured the chairman and Nigerians that due process would be considered in selling the houses. Represented by the Permanent Secretary of the ministry, Alhaji Bashir Nura Alkali, the minister said all people interested should apply through a portal of the ministry. 